acf.head_text:
With the growing complexity of infrastructures and applications, adding observability to the mix is becoming necessary for organizations of any size. It is the only way for them to fully understand their systems, help minimize downtime and allow developers to quickly get to the root cause of problems. But as with anything, it also comes with a cost, both in terms of financial investment and the time needed for setting up these observability tools. Fortunately, regardless of the type of architecture used – microservices-based, Kubernetes, public cloud, hardware or traditional IT stack – there are growing solutions available which can meet their requirements.

In this article, we will look at 10 observability tools worth paying attention to in 2023.

&nbsp;
